<hl>
<seg id=1> Contribute science and technology achievements to people Wangma computer "opens" its software to China </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> This newspaper, Beijing, January 5 (reporter: Huang Biao).  On January 4th,  Wangma Computer Company, a hi-tech enterprise based in Zhongguancun, Beijing, held a press conference in People' Great Conference Hall.  Wangma publicized that in order to satisfy the urgent demand for office automation of the party, government, and army, the whole line of "Wangma Digital Essence" of over RMB1 million profit would be offered free of charge. Wangma announced that it intends to distribute its software with non-encrypted disks inside the country; hence any computer user might copy and use it. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Wangma Computer Company was named after the Chinese character coding method invented by famous computer specialist Wang Yongmin known as the "Wubi character input". </seg>
<seg id=4> The simple and highly effective input method had reached more than 85% of all computer users in the country, and has become the leading Chinese character input software. </seg>
<seg id=5> With the rapid increase in computer use, more and more computer users have registered to purchase the new edition of the "Wubi character model" and the Wangma Chinese character operation system. </seg>
<seg id=6> In order to benefit society, Wangma Computer Company decided to give up the opportunity to make a large profit, and rather distributed the non-encrypted disk to users and allows them to copy it freely. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Government leaders, specialists, and users alike have applauded Wangma Computer Company's selfless decision. </seg>
</p>
